    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe background highlight of `reverse` is not retained for floating windows when `winblend`>0.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean example.vim\r\n```\r\n\r\nAdd the following code, which opens a floating window and sets its highlighting to `StatusLine`:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nlet buf = nvim_create_buf(v:false, v:true)\r\nlet popup = nvim_open_win(buf, 0, {\r\n      \\   'relative':  'editor',\r\n      \\   'row':       15,\r\n      \\   'col':       5,\r\n      \\   'width':     20,\r\n      \\   'height':    1,\r\n      \\   'focusable': v:true,\r\n      \\   'style':     'minimal',\r\n      \\   'border':    'single',\r\n      \\ })\r\ncall setwinvar(popup, '&winhighlight', 'Normal:StatusLine')\r\n```\r\n\r\nSource the code.\r\n\r\n```\r\n:source %\r\n```\r\n\r\nA floating window with `StatusLine` highlighting appears.\r\n\r\n![Screenshot_20230626_185826](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/541289/509b4a65-e0c8-4146-8466-370972a2e1aa)\r\n\r\nNext, navigate to the window and `:set winblend=1`. The `StatusLine` background highlighting (`reverse`) is not retained.\r\n\r\n![Screenshot_20230626_185918](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/541289/694027a0-fb6d-47f7-be07-bf8eef966ca6)\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI expected that the background color would not be lost with `winblend`>0. For other highlight groups where the background is not `reverse`, changing the `winblend` does not modify the background color (rather, it modifies the displayed color of the text from the window beneath if it overlaps).\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.9.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nKubuntu 23.04\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nKonsole 22.12.3\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nappimage",
